This paper is primarily focused on visual recognition tasks using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel deep architecture that incorporates Fisher Vector encoding with Variational Auto-Encoder (FV-VAE), which involves training a deep generative model in an end-to-end manner. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Furthermore, the experiments conducted in the paper involve video action recognition and fine-grained image classification, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of stochastic gradient methods for optimization, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
